{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`VimEditor` currently snapshots Pi TUI's original hardware cursor visibility, writes DECSCUSR cursor-shape hints, and calls `setShowHardwareCursor(true)` whenever the effective cursor style is `bar`. This fixed invisible bar cursors, but it also means Pi's `positionHardwareCursor()` shows a real blinking terminal cursor at every render that includes `CURSOR_MARKER`. During agent work, assistant/tool components render frequently while the prompt editor can still be focused and can still emit `CUR"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": "line 14", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Suppress visible hardware cursor flicker while agent work is running."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": "line 31", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### 1. Gate hardware cursor visibility by agent busy state in `VimEditor` Target seams: `src/vim-editor.ts`, `test/vim-editor.test.ts`."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_1_gate_hardware_cursor_visibility_by_agent_busy_state_in_vimeditor", "label": "1. Gate hardware cursor visibility by agent busy state in VimEditor", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": "line 33", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/vim-editor.ts`, `test/vim-editor.test.ts`. Add a small runtime policy to `VimEditor`:"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_2_drive_busy_idle_from_lifecycle_agentstart_and_agentend", "label": "2. Drive busy/idle from lifecycle agentstart and agentend", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": "line 53", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/lifecycle.ts`, `test/lifecycle.test.ts`. Widen tracked editor shape from reset-only to cursor-lifecycle methods. On `agent_start`, call `setAgentBusy(true)` on every tracked editor. On `agent_end`, call `setAgentBusy(false)` before or during the existing install path so newly interactive prompts restore the current cursor policy. On shutdown or disable, reset tracked editors as today."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_3_preserve_render_width_safety_and_docs_source_of_truth", "label": "3. Preserve render width safety and docs source-of-truth", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": "line 67", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/render.ts`, `test/render.test.ts`, `docs/features.md`, `TODOS.md`. Prefer no render output change. If implementation requires a fallback fake cursor adjustment, keep `visibleWidth(renderCursorCell(...)) === 1`, keep underlying character preservation, and keep `CURSOR_MARKER` placement unchanged. Document only observable user-facing cursor behavior, not internal lifecycle plumbing. Mark `TODOS.md` complete only after validation passes."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": "line 78", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- Agent event ordering differs from expectation \u2192 Mitigate with lifecycle tests for `agent_start` before any editor exists, existing editors, new editor creation after busy state, `agent_end`, and shutdown. - Hardware cursor remains hidden after a failed or interrupted agent turn \u2192 Mitigate by restoring on `agent_end`, resetting on `session_shutdown`, and keeping `/vimmode off` reset behavior. - Bar cursor becomes less visible during a small window before `agent_end` \u2192 Acceptable because user is"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_migration_plan", "label": "Migration Plan", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": "line 86", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1. Add focused tests for `VimEditor` busy/idle visibility policy while `insert` uses `bar`, including original visibility true/false cases and reset behavior. 2. Extend lifecycle tracking and tests for `agent_start`, `agent_end`, shutdown, delayed install, and `/vimmode off`. 3. Implement the minimal adapter/lifecycle changes."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_open_questions", "label": "Open Questions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": "line 96", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- If a future Pi version exposes a direct \"prompt input disabled\" or \"agent busy\" editor prop, should pi-vimmode switch from lifecycle calls to that source? Current plan stays on public lifecycle events. - If a terminal still flickers with busy suppression, should a later change add an opt-in `piVimMode.cursor.hardwareCursor` policy? Not part of this change unless validation proves necessary."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_ref_src_vim_editor_ts", "label": "vim-editor.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": "line 9", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_ref_src_lifecycle_ts", "label": "lifecycle.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": "line 10", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_ref_src_render_ts", "label": "render.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": "line 11", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_ref_test_vim_editor_test_ts", "label": "vim-editor.test.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-todos-cursor-flicker/design.md", "source_location": "line 12", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_fix_todos_cursor_flicker_design_ref_test_lifecycle_test_ts", "label": "lifecycle.test.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-fix-